File: e2e/dispatch-resilience.e2e.ts

fakeWs leak (lines 296-329, 341-352, 538-548): In the 'Tool call during reconnect window' tests and 'server-side dispatch timeout' test, a fakeWs WebSocket is created and closed linearly. If waitForLog() throws (times out), fakeWs.close() is never reached. The leaked WebSocket holds the extension's connection slot, preventing reconnection. Wrap in try/finally:

const fakeWs = ...;
try {
  await waitForLog(...);
  fakeWs.close();
  // assertions
} catch (e) {
  fakeWs.close();
  throw e;
}

rawWs leak (lines 732-779): In 'Malformed WebSocket messages' test, rawWs is created at line 735 and closed at line 779. If expect(pongReceived).toBe(true) at line 776 fails, rawWs.close() is never reached. Move rawWs.close() before the assertion, or wrap in try/finally.

File: e2e/dispatch-resilience.e2e.ts

timeoutClient leak (lines 501-566): The test creates timeoutClient at line 504 and closes it at line 566. If an assertion fails before line 566, the session leaks. Wrap the entire body after initialize() in try/finally with timeoutClient.close() in finally.

Fixed 2s sleep (lines 670-678): After firing the tool call, the test sleeps 2s before closing the tab. Under heavy CI load, 2s may not be enough for the request to reach the test server. Replace with the same polling pattern used at line 520-532:

await waitFor(
  async () => {
    const invocations = await testServer.invocations();
    return invocations.some(i => i.path === '/api/echo');
  },
  10_000, 200,
  'echo request to reach test server'
);

Import waitFor from '../helpers.js' if not already imported.
